description.p:
(1) to identify a server with a relatively high probability of exceeding a bandwidth by predicting the quantity of traffic of each pod;
(2) to select a pod to be moved and a move destination server in a manner that the quantity of traffic is distributed among the servers; and
(3) at (2), to, after scaling out (dividing) the pod into a plurality of pieces and distributing the quantity of traffic among the pods, re-execute the procedure of and after (2), if there is not a server that satisfies conditions as a move destination.
